Title: As an unauthenticated user, I can search for a product, so that I can find what I am looking for easier
Description:
Acceptance Criteria:
Given that I am an unauthenticated user,
When I navigate to the home page and enter a phrase into the search bar,
Then I receive a list of related products

What you need to do:

This depends on [SD-47](https://linear.app/sd-project/issue/SD-47/as-an-unauthenticated-user-i-can-view-all-the-products-available-on).

You need to edit the product gallery component so that it has a search bar and uses a simple text based search. This can be done with filters.
Creator: 2555154@students.wits.ac.za

Title: As an unauthenticated user, I can view all the products available on the site, so that I can see which ones I want.
Description:
Acceptance Criteria:
Given that I am an unauthenticated user,
when I navigate to the home page,
then I can scroll down and view a gallery of all the products.

What to do:

1. creating a product component.
   you need to create a product component which contains all the information related to a product. (you may have to create types, sub-components etc. use discretion)
2. creating a product gallery component.
   you need to create a product gallery component which contains a scroll-able collection of a list of products. (you may have to create types, sub-components etc. use discretion)
3. You need to add or edit the page.tsx file in the root of app folder. Making sure it has and renders the product gallery component.
4. you need to consume the /products route from the backend. You can use useEffect and useState hooks for the fetch functionality. 

You need to build these out in jsx using shadcn ui components.
Creator: 2555154@students.wits.ac.za

Title: Create the scenario diagram for all existing and upcoming user stories
Description:
**Acceptance Criteria:**

Each of the 4 user stories in sprint 1 ([SD-23](https://linear.app/sd-project/issue/SD-23/as-a-user-i-want-to-be-able-to-sign-up-as-an-admin-and-get-a), [SD-24](https://linear.app/sd-project/issue/SD-24/as-a-seller-i-want-to-signup-and-login-so-that-i-can-be-able-to-access), [SD-25](https://linear.app/sd-project/issue/SD-25/as-a-buyer-i-want-to-sign-up-and-login-to-my-account-so-that-i-can-buy) [SD-36](https://linear.app/sd-project/issue/SD-36/as-an-admin-i-want-to-be-able-to-escalate-privileges-so-that-the))  is covered in the scenario diagram.

Each of the 7 user stories in sprint 2() are covered in the scenario diagram.

**What you need to do:**

In draw.io you need to create a scenario diagram which encompases the above. 
Refer to slides_5 in course on what a scenario diagram is.
Creator: 2555154@students.wits.ac.za
